1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:05,400
Can I ask you for the Klaikot Lek Lai?

2
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,960
<i>I know that without the Klaikot Lek Lai,</i>

3
00:02:08,039 --> 00:02:09,680
<i>you'll lose your sorcery.</i>

4
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:12,400
Please help us defeat evil.

5
00:02:12,480 --> 00:02:14,480
<i>I'll forge it into a dagger.</i>

6
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:16,280
<i>Go destroy their Lek Lai forging ritual.</i>

7
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:17,440
Go!

8
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:20,200
Stab its heart.

9
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:25,680
<i>Bring the dagger to me,</i>

10
00:02:25,760 --> 00:02:28,560
<i>along with Yiam's head</i>
<i>and his companions'.</i>

11
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:30,040
Hey!

12
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:33,760
<i>Matiyano matiya matithi sodhaya sapasa.</i>

13
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:35,160
Petch knows now.

14
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:36,960
That's why he sent men
to seize the dagger.

15
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:38,120
<i>I'll be waiting to see</i>

16
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:41,200
<i>how you withstand my army of the dead.</i>

17
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,480
Lasor.

18
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:02,080
That's not Lasor, Dad.

19
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:17,440
Of course.

20
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:21,720
How could he be here?

21
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:27,320
You're worried about him. I know.

22
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:30,880
What father wouldn't worry
about his child?

23
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:36,000
Even if I was stubborn
and never said it out loud,

24
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:40,680
there hasn't been a single day
I didn't worry about him.

25
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:45,440
If Lasor heard that,

26
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,440
he'd be happy.

27
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:54,400
The reason he strayed so far…

28
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:59,920
perhaps I'm to blame.

29
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:04,240
I never showed him that I loved him.

30
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,720
So he did everything he could

31
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:10,720
just to earn my love.

32
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:14,600
Why would you do this?
I finally found a way to learn magic.

33
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:17,279
So you'd learn filthy,
cursed magic like this?

34
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:20,800
Ruining yourself isn't enough. You'd drag
everyone else down with you too.

35
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:22,320
Even if you're my son,

36
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:25,640
if you break the rules,
I won't let it slide.

37
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:29,120
Get out of my Chum Suea.

38
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,960
If I could turn back time,

39
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:39,400
I'd try to understand him.

40
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:41,840
I'd show him

41
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,640
that I love him.

42
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:50,120
Please don't blame yourself

43
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:53,280
for what can't be undone.

44
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:55,760
These days,

45
00:04:56,560 --> 00:05:00,200
I see you doing everything

46
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:03,280
to bring Lasor back.

47
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:08,800
I think he knows

48
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:12,480
how much you love him.

49
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:20,640
It's not too late, is it?

50
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:27,080
If I want to atone to you and to Lasor.

51
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:40,560
Yiwha,

52
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:43,640
go call Yiam for me.

53
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:04,120
Yiam.

54
00:06:04,680 --> 00:06:07,240
I'm going to pass my sorcery to you.

55
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:08,400
Dad!

56
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:11,280
Why?

57
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:13,560
Because you are the most suitable.

58
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,800
The sorcery of Khao Phrom

59
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,720
should belong to a good man,

60
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:23,720
one who helps those in need.

61
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:29,120
But you already use your magic
to help people.

62
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:31,000
I am a bandit.

63
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:34,360
Even if

64
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:37,960
I rob the rich to help the poor,

65
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:42,120
it still defies morality,
righteousness, and the law.

66
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:46,320
I am not worthy of the sorcery

67
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:49,120
Old Master Khrua Phut entrusted to me.

68
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:51,280
If you give it up,

69
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:54,080
who will lead?

70
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,520
You and Yiam.

71
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:00,320
Take care of everyone.

72
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:04,600
I want you to reconsider.

73
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:06,920
Prepare yourself.

74
00:07:08,320 --> 00:07:13,040
Tonight, I will pass it to you.

75
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,840
Dad must want you to have sorcery

76
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:31,680
to protect me.

77
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:36,400
I believe he's thinking beyond that.

78
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:38,800
If he gives it all to you…

79
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,600
will he be alright?

80
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,160
You're really going to
pass your sorcery to Yiam?

81
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:05,800
You don't have to give him all of it.

82
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:09,200
Keep some for emergencies.

83
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:21,440
<i>Yamahang khru achariyang saranang.</i>

84
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:02,080
Dad!

85
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:03,960
Dad.

86
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:08,480
Wad.

87
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:14,320
I've passed all my sorcery to you.

88
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:20,160
Only you can fight Petch now.

89
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:25,640
Don't worry, Father.

90
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,840
I will find a way to save Lasor

91
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:31,760
and bring down Phraya Kaipetch.

92
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:34,680
Dad.

93
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:38,720
Birth, aging, sickness, death,
these are natural.

94
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:41,400
No one escapes them.

95
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:44,920
Don't worry about me.

96
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:49,120
Prepare yourself.

97
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:51,880
Yes, Father.

98
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:02,120
Dad. Dad.

99
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:04,920
Dad.

100
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:10,560
Dad. Dad!

101
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:37,120
Father.

102
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:44,800
Dad,

103
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:49,560
Yiam brewed some medicine for you.
Please drink it.

104
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:02,920
You must rest well
to regain your strength.

105
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:05,800
Yiam,

106
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:09,840
the sorcery I passed to you

107
00:11:09,920 --> 00:11:11,760
will grow stronger

108
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:15,280
if you train
your body and mind diligently.

109
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:21,520
Yes, Father. I won't disappoint you.

110
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:25,000
I feel sorry for Yod,

111
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:29,240
that he never lived to see
the strong man you've become.

112
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:32,120
I regret as well

113
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:37,440
that he wasn't here to see me
become village chief as he wished.

114
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:43,280
Whenever I think of that night,

115
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:46,200
I still regret

116
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:50,160
that I couldn't reach him in time.

117
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:55,240
That was in the past. Don't dwell on it.

118
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:59,840
I'm no longer angry.
I don't hate anyone anymore.

119
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:12,000
Yiwha brought me back to who I once was.

120
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:16,360
Yiwha's love made me realize

121
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:19,080
that a heart that forgives

122
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:22,000
is far lighter
than one that clings to hatred.

123
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:33,680
Right high.

124
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:35,360
Left high.

125
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:36,880
Through the middle.

126
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:46,240
Grip the tip here.

127
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:49,040
When you aim, hold near the tip.

128
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:51,160
Draw back, then strike.

129
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,760
Before firing,

130
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:57,400
check your weapon

131
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:59,400
Aim at your target.

132
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:00,600
Shoot.

133
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:35,240
The Klaikot Lek Lai dagger is sacred.

134
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:40,160
Use it with mindfulness.
Stand firm in virtue,

135
00:13:41,160 --> 00:13:44,960
and you will overcome all evil.

136
00:13:56,160 --> 00:13:59,520
May goodness be the shield
that protects us all.

137
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,200
Our people are ready.

138
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:04,200
We await only your command, Father Wad.

139
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:09,000
Petch must be preparing a counterattack.

140
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:13,440
I'm worried about Lasor.

141
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:15,920
Lasor will be safe.

142
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:19,800
The Lek Lai dagger
will not harm one who remains good.

143
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:35,240
Eat.

144
00:14:38,560 --> 00:14:41,280
You'll need strength
to fight Bandit Wad and his men.

145
00:14:45,640 --> 00:14:47,840
Like moths drawn to flame.

146
00:14:48,880 --> 00:14:50,000
The moment you arrive

147
00:14:50,960 --> 00:14:52,320
is the moment you die.

148
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:20,360
Our land has fallen into chaos

149
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:23,560
because wicked men crave power.

150
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:27,680
The time has come to repay our homeland.

151
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:30,160
Let us unite,

152
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:31,640
overthrow the tyrant

153
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:34,200
who sells our land and our people.

154
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:39,600
I, on behalf of Khun Yod Pakdee,

155
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,000
will lead you into battle today.

156
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:55,240
May Heaven and Earth

157
00:15:56,920 --> 00:15:59,040
grant us

158
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:02,640
victory over our enemies.

159
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:19,200
The heavens bear witness.

160
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:22,920
We shall be victorious!

161
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:26,440
Yeah!

162
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:38,840
Everyone, stop.

163
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,360
What is it, Yiam?

164
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:45,520
Something's not right in this forest.

165
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:50,200
There isn't a single bird or animal.

166
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:54,960
Tell everyone to prepare.

167
00:17:00,680 --> 00:17:02,240
Where are they hiding, Pun?

168
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:04,119
How should I know?

169
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,599
Over there!

170
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:14,079
Stay alert. They're ambushing us.

171
00:17:21,359 --> 00:17:23,760
We're at a disadvantage.
We can't see them.

172
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:28,440
They're using a concealment spell.

173
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:30,760
You must use the Sema-dispelling spell.

174
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:34,040
to cleanse their sorcery and break it.

175
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:44,760
<i>Ewang ehi na khluean mo thon</i>

176
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:47,200
<i>phut khlon tha thon ya lut loi luean</i>

177
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:48,920
<i>khluean duai namo buddhaya</i>

178
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,240
<i>yathaphut mona.</i>

179
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:12,360
Their skin is too tough.

180
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:14,280
Normal bullets won't pierce them.

181
00:18:14,360 --> 00:18:16,760
Even my enchanted rounds have no effect.

182
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:21,040
<i>Thusa ma ti.</i>

183
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:41,920
May the sacred power within this dagger

184
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:44,520
destroy all evil.

185
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:13,920
These aren't ordinary corpses.

186
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:17,120
He must have used sacred water
made from the bones of a violent ghost

187
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,760
to bind those bandits

188
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:21,040
into undead servants.

189
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:23,520
Petch sent them to block us

190
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:24,920
from reaching Lasor.

191
00:19:26,080 --> 00:19:28,280
We're running out of time.

192
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:32,200
We must stop Phraya Kaipetch
before he fully takes over Lasor's body.

193
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:59,480
Pun, Chang, upstairs.

194
00:19:59,560 --> 00:20:01,120
Yiwha, that way.

195
00:20:25,080 --> 00:20:27,080
There's not a trace of Phraya Kaipetch.

196
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:28,800
Did he run?

197
00:20:29,760 --> 00:20:31,400
He's using a concealment spell.

198
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:33,760
That's why we can't see him.

199
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:38,280
Yiam, can you cast
the Sema-dispelling spell again?

200
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:44,640
It only works if I know where he's hiding.

201
00:20:47,320 --> 00:20:51,760
If we don't know his location,
what do we do?

202
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:00,880
Lasor.

203
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:12,640
<i>Lasor, help me.</i>

204
00:21:14,040 --> 00:21:15,600
<i>Where are you?</i>

205
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:19,640
<i>I'm here.</i>

206
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:21,240
<i>I'm right here.</i>

207
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:22,560
Lasor.

208
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:23,920
Yiwha.

209
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:31,720
Yiwha, wait.

210
00:21:56,200 --> 00:21:57,600
What is it, Yiwha?

211
00:21:58,120 --> 00:22:00,000
I heard Lasor's voice,

212
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:02,840
but now it's gone.

213
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,160
Petch must be close.

214
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:19,440
<i>Ewang ehi na khluean mo thon</i>
<i>phut khlon tha thon</i>

215
00:22:19,520 --> 00:22:23,320
<i>ya lut loi luean khluean duai</i>
<i>namo buddhaya yathaphut mona.</i>

216
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:47,840
You're pretty impressive, Yiam.

217
00:22:50,480 --> 00:22:52,160
Oh, Wad…

218
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:56,080
Even after transferring all your sorcery
to your son-in-law,

219
00:22:56,160 --> 00:22:59,000
you still can't touch me.

220
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:00,680
Today,

221
00:23:02,560 --> 00:23:07,120
I'll make you pay for what you did to me.

222
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:11,920
<i>Watch me.</i>
<i>One day I'll rise to power again.</i>

223
00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:15,240
I will return and make you pay

224
00:23:15,320 --> 00:23:16,400
for everything.

225
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:21,440
How many lives have you taken for revenge?

226
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:24,880
Old Master, Yod,

227
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:27,960
his wife, his daughter, even Niem.

228
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:31,880
Tell me, has it really
extinguished the fire in your heart?

229
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:33,160
A bandit like you

230
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:36,320
dares preach to me?

231
00:23:38,080 --> 00:23:40,280
You buried me alive.

232
00:23:40,360 --> 00:23:43,360
Today, I'll return the favor.

233
00:23:44,480 --> 00:23:46,000
If you hate me,

234
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:50,440
take it out on me.
My son has nothing to do with this.

235
00:23:54,520 --> 00:23:55,400
Fine.

236
00:23:56,680 --> 00:24:00,360
Then bow at my feet.

237
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:04,040
Bow and I'll spare Lasor.

238
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:08,160
Think of it as mercy for a fledgling bird.

239
00:24:08,760 --> 00:24:09,800
Come on.

240
00:24:10,360 --> 00:24:11,960
Bow at my feet.

241
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:18,920
Don't, Dad.

242
00:24:19,080 --> 00:24:21,040
Lasor and I would rather die

243
00:24:21,120 --> 00:24:23,240
than bow to you!

244
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:52,360
- Yiam.
- Yiam.

245
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:53,480
- Yiam.
- Yiam.

246
00:24:55,560 --> 00:24:56,480
Hey!

247
00:25:11,840 --> 00:25:13,080
Wad.

248
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:19,800
Are you a tiger or a dog?

249
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:23,480
How does it feel beneath my foot?

250
00:25:31,480 --> 00:25:32,920
Get up.

251
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:44,760
Today, you two

252
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:48,040
will join Yod

253
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:51,360
and Niem, your dear friends.

254
00:25:58,160 --> 00:26:00,480
Let go of me. Let go of me, Wad!

255
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:08,000
Wad!

256
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:11,600
Let go of me!

257
00:26:12,200 --> 00:26:13,320
Let go!

258
00:26:47,560 --> 00:26:49,120
Lasor.

259
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:54,720
Lasor. Lasor.

260
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:00,040
Lasor.

261
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:03,600
I… I didn't mean to.

262
00:27:08,840 --> 00:27:10,000
You did the right thing.

263
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:13,160
You set me free.

264
00:27:21,120 --> 00:27:22,520
Lasor.

265
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:36,640
He's getting away.

266
00:27:46,440 --> 00:27:48,360
<i>Amang kasinang atitami.</i>

267
00:27:56,440 --> 00:28:00,480
<i>Meddling fool.</i>
<i>Then I'll take your body instead.</i>

268
00:28:02,560 --> 00:28:04,000
<i>Sam pa chit cha mi.</i>

269
00:28:26,720 --> 00:28:27,560
Go, Yiwha.

270
00:28:30,040 --> 00:28:31,240
Go.

271
00:28:36,120 --> 00:28:37,800
You have to help Dad, Yiwha.

272
00:28:44,400 --> 00:28:45,360
Wad.

273
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:49,360
<i>I'll drag you to hell with me!</i>

274
00:28:52,720 --> 00:28:53,760
Wad.

275
00:28:54,640 --> 00:28:56,040
- Wad.
- Dad.

276
00:29:00,040 --> 00:29:01,160
Yiwha,

277
00:29:02,160 --> 00:29:04,000
stab me in the heart now.

278
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:07,720
No, Dad.

279
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:10,680
I can't.

280
00:29:11,680 --> 00:29:14,200
Yiwha, listen to me.

281
00:29:14,880 --> 00:29:17,960
You have to do it. You must!

282
00:29:18,040 --> 00:29:19,480
I can't!

283
00:29:20,480 --> 00:29:24,640
Yiwha, do it! There's no time!

284
00:29:33,680 --> 00:29:35,880
Dad! No! Dad!

285
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:48,880
Dad!

286
00:30:00,480 --> 00:30:01,320
Dad!

287
00:30:08,920 --> 00:30:10,000
Dad.

288
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:11,160
Father Wad.

289
00:30:21,080 --> 00:30:22,440
Chaem…

290
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:28,080
I kept the soul-transfer spell.

291
00:30:30,960 --> 00:30:33,360
I didn't pass it to Yiam,

292
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:35,920
just as you told me.

293
00:30:37,080 --> 00:30:39,400
You're really going to
pass your sorcery to Yiam?

294
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:43,800
You don't have to give him all of it.

295
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:46,600
Keep some for emergencies.

296
00:30:48,880 --> 00:30:51,240
We did it.

297
00:30:53,680 --> 00:30:55,160
I killed Petch.

298
00:30:56,120 --> 00:30:58,000
Everyone has been avenged.

299
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:02,120
Dad…

300
00:31:02,840 --> 00:31:05,960
don't die. Please.

301
00:31:06,640 --> 00:31:08,560
Don't blame yourself, Yiwha.

302
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:12,760
This isn't your fault.

303
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:16,200
This is my fate.

304
00:31:17,240 --> 00:31:19,520
It was always meant to be.

305
00:31:20,560 --> 00:31:22,040
Don't move yet.

306
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:24,480
I'll find herbs to treat you.

307
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:26,520
Yiam…

308
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:30,880
it's useless.

309
00:31:33,680 --> 00:31:37,160
I know my body. My time has come.

310
00:31:40,920 --> 00:31:44,000
Yiwha… Lasor…

311
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:48,240
After your mother passed,

312
00:31:48,320 --> 00:31:50,000
and that prophecy followed us,

313
00:31:53,040 --> 00:31:55,760
I never knew how to raise you two

314
00:31:56,720 --> 00:31:58,760
into good people.

315
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:03,080
I'm a bandit.

316
00:32:05,360 --> 00:32:08,040
I've sinned again and again.

317
00:32:10,520 --> 00:32:12,560
All I could think was

318
00:32:13,480 --> 00:32:17,440
that I didn't want you

319
00:32:18,360 --> 00:32:21,360
to grow up in Chum Suea.

320
00:32:26,760 --> 00:32:28,840
So I pushed you.

321
00:32:30,760 --> 00:32:33,920
I was harsh.

322
00:32:36,760 --> 00:32:39,680
It was because of me.

323
00:32:39,760 --> 00:32:42,880
No, Dad. It was my fault.

324
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:45,480
I chose this path.

325
00:32:49,960 --> 00:32:51,720
I'm sorry.

326
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:59,480
Is it too late

327
00:33:00,680 --> 00:33:03,400
to ask for your forgiveness?

328
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:11,440
No, Dad.

329
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:14,680
Please don't say that.

330
00:33:15,720 --> 00:33:19,840
I know now how much you love me.

331
00:33:25,600 --> 00:33:27,000
Yiam…

332
00:33:29,320 --> 00:33:30,960
Promise me…

333
00:33:33,760 --> 00:33:36,800
you'll take the best care of Yiwha.

334
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:41,080
No.

335
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:45,120
You have to stay with me, with Yiwha.

336
00:33:47,120 --> 00:33:50,520
You have to live
to hold your grandchild, our child.

337
00:33:53,360 --> 00:33:54,520
Promise me.

338
00:34:03,560 --> 00:34:05,120
I promise, Father.

339
00:34:07,960 --> 00:34:10,000
- Dad.
- Dad.

340
00:34:22,520 --> 00:34:24,480
Your mother has come for me.

341
00:34:29,920 --> 00:34:31,199
Panan…

342
00:34:33,840 --> 00:34:35,120
Dad.

343
00:34:37,080 --> 00:34:39,639
I've missed you so much.

344
00:34:41,560 --> 00:34:44,239
No…

345
00:34:59,880 --> 00:35:00,920
Dad.

346
00:35:06,160 --> 00:35:09,560
- Dad. Dad!
- Wad.

347
00:35:10,320 --> 00:35:11,520
Dad!

348
00:35:39,720 --> 00:35:42,120
Yiwha!

349
00:35:42,960 --> 00:35:45,880
Yiwha. Yiwha!

350
00:35:59,560 --> 00:36:00,680
Lasor.

351
00:36:03,240 --> 00:36:04,120
Yiwha.

352
00:36:07,920 --> 00:36:09,440
Where are we?

353
00:36:12,640 --> 00:36:14,040
I think…

354
00:36:16,520 --> 00:36:18,040
this is the world after death.

355
00:36:25,240 --> 00:36:26,440
Lasor…

356
00:36:29,200 --> 00:36:30,360
I'm sorry.

357
00:36:40,240 --> 00:36:42,120
Stop blaming yourself, Yiwha.

358
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:45,320
I'm the one who should apologize.

359
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:52,160
I dragged you into hardship,
into the same boat as me.

360
00:36:54,640 --> 00:36:56,160
My sins are too heavy.

361
00:36:57,360 --> 00:36:58,760
I killed Dad

362
00:37:00,280 --> 00:37:01,840
and my brother.

363
00:37:03,920 --> 00:37:05,040
No, Yiwha.

364
00:37:06,240 --> 00:37:09,960
You never meant to kill Dad.
You never meant to kill me.

365
00:37:11,120 --> 00:37:13,080
You were trying to destroy evil,
to stop Phraya Kaipetch,

366
00:37:13,160 --> 00:37:16,280
to save me,
to save the people of Tha Khiri.

367
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:24,040
If you hadn't helped me,
I could never have done it.

368
00:37:28,240 --> 00:37:32,120
Whatever awaits us, heaven or hell,

369
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:34,320
I'll go with you.

370
00:37:59,120 --> 00:38:00,520
What happened, Pun?

371
00:38:08,120 --> 00:38:09,760
How is she?

372
00:38:10,440 --> 00:38:12,720
Their pulses are weakening.

373
00:38:12,800 --> 00:38:15,600
Why must Yiwha suffer

374
00:38:15,680 --> 00:38:17,280
alongside Lasor?

375
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:20,760
As long as her pulse still beats,

376
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:23,160
I won't give up.

377
00:38:34,600 --> 00:38:35,880
Yiam.

378
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:37,920
Here, Sab Suea leaves.
They might stop the bleeding.

379
00:38:39,880 --> 00:38:40,920
Help me.

380
00:39:11,200 --> 00:39:13,160
Please come back to me, Yiwha.

381
00:39:27,120 --> 00:39:28,120
Yiwha,

382
00:39:29,160 --> 00:39:31,480
we may be siblings,

383
00:39:31,560 --> 00:39:33,560
but we are as different
as Heaven and the abyss.

384
00:39:34,200 --> 00:39:36,520
You've always been kind.
You never harmed anyone.

385
00:39:37,360 --> 00:39:38,640
Unlike me,

386
00:39:39,600 --> 00:39:41,400
I've committed countless sins.

387
00:39:45,200 --> 00:39:49,240
My destination can only be hell.

388
00:39:53,120 --> 00:39:57,440
No matter which pit awaits us,
I'll go there with you.

389
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:07,360
- Yiwha!
- Lasor.

390
00:40:11,920 --> 00:40:13,560
Lasor.

391
00:40:16,040 --> 00:40:17,080
Go away!

392
00:40:19,560 --> 00:40:21,360
- What are those things?
- Watch out, Yiwha.

393
00:40:27,960 --> 00:40:30,760
Yiwha, I'm glad

394
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:32,760
I was born your brother.

395
00:40:32,840 --> 00:40:34,200
Now go.

396
00:40:39,280 --> 00:40:40,520
Lasor!

397
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:45,280
Lasor!

398
00:41:09,560 --> 00:41:10,400
Yiwha.

399
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:13,440
Yiwha's awake.

400
00:41:18,160 --> 00:41:20,000
What happened to me?

401
00:41:20,720 --> 00:41:22,600
Your heart stopped for a moment.

402
00:41:23,280 --> 00:41:24,840
It's a miracle you came back.

403
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:35,920
And Lasor?

404
00:43:33,640 --> 00:43:35,440
It's not too burned today.

405
00:43:37,920 --> 00:43:39,120
Still edible.

406
00:43:40,320 --> 00:43:43,760
If your mother were still alive,
she'd be so happy

407
00:43:44,880 --> 00:43:48,240
to see you two lying on my lap like this.

408
00:44:57,880 --> 00:44:59,600
Because you are good at heart,

409
00:45:00,480 --> 00:45:03,000
the Lek Lai Klaikot dagger
could not harm you.

410
00:45:04,520 --> 00:45:07,160
No, it was you

411
00:45:07,760 --> 00:45:09,720
who brought me back.

412
00:45:28,880 --> 00:45:30,240
Lasor.

413
00:45:31,240 --> 00:45:33,240
You can't leave me.

414
00:45:33,760 --> 00:45:35,400
You have to come back.

415
00:45:37,320 --> 00:45:38,360
Lasor…

416
00:45:39,320 --> 00:45:41,080
Yiam. Yiam.

417
00:45:41,960 --> 00:45:45,960
You need to help Lasor. Please. I beg you.

418
00:45:46,760 --> 00:45:49,240
Try one more time.

419
00:45:49,920 --> 00:45:51,080
Yiwha.

420
00:45:53,760 --> 00:45:55,400
I've tried everything.

421
00:46:06,280 --> 00:46:09,160
When we were in Chum Suea,

422
00:46:09,720 --> 00:46:12,120
you left me once,

423
00:46:13,400 --> 00:46:15,960
but I found you again.

424
00:46:17,640 --> 00:46:20,360
But this time, you've gone too far.

425
00:46:20,840 --> 00:46:23,520
I don't know when we'll meet again.

426
00:46:46,160 --> 00:46:47,440
Yiwha.

427
00:46:51,720 --> 00:46:53,120
Lasor.

428
00:46:54,880 --> 00:46:55,920
Lasor.

429
00:47:04,400 --> 00:47:05,600
Yiwha…

430
00:47:19,280 --> 00:47:23,080
I returned to life because of you.

431
00:47:24,520 --> 00:47:26,520
If anything had happened to you,

432
00:47:27,880 --> 00:47:30,800
I could never forgive myself.

433
00:47:31,400 --> 00:47:33,800
How long will you remain ordained?

434
00:47:36,240 --> 00:47:37,920
I intend

435
00:47:38,840 --> 00:47:42,760
to serve beneath the saffron robe

436
00:47:43,560 --> 00:47:45,160
until my final breath.

437
00:47:52,280 --> 00:47:55,720
My father once wished that I be ordained

438
00:47:56,480 --> 00:47:59,960
and journey to Lanka to begin anew.

439
00:48:00,040 --> 00:48:02,080
So

440
00:48:02,160 --> 00:48:04,400
I will fulfill his wish,

441
00:48:04,480 --> 00:48:07,040
study the Dhamma diligently

442
00:48:07,120 --> 00:48:08,840
and dedicate merit

443
00:48:08,920 --> 00:48:11,960
to my departed parents.

444
00:48:20,840 --> 00:48:24,440
The boat to Lanka is departing, Venerable.

445
00:48:26,680 --> 00:48:29,640
I must go now. If fate allows,

446
00:48:30,840 --> 00:48:32,280
we shall meet again.

447
00:49:23,960 --> 00:49:25,960
These herbs are both food and medicine.

448
00:49:26,040 --> 00:49:29,520
I'll share what I learned
from the scriptures at Khao Phrom

449
00:49:29,600 --> 00:49:31,840
with the villagers

450
00:49:31,920 --> 00:49:35,360
so they can care for themselves
and stay free from illness.

451
00:49:36,280 --> 00:49:40,560
Each day, you become more
like Khun Yod Pakdee, your father.

452
00:49:42,920 --> 00:49:44,720
I never understood

453
00:49:45,400 --> 00:49:48,080
why Dad worked himself to exhaustion
helping others

454
00:49:49,400 --> 00:49:51,960
until I realized true happiness

455
00:49:52,920 --> 00:49:55,160
comes from serving people.

456
00:49:56,680 --> 00:49:58,800
Your father wasn't different from mine.

457
00:49:59,480 --> 00:50:02,000
But mine chose the path of a bandit

458
00:50:02,080 --> 00:50:05,600
to fight injustice in this land.

459
00:50:06,640 --> 00:50:10,080
We all have a duty to repay our homeland.

460
00:50:15,600 --> 00:50:16,600
Yiwha.

461
00:50:17,240 --> 00:50:18,600
Are you alright?

462
00:50:20,120 --> 00:50:21,640
I suddenly feel dizzy.

463
00:50:23,840 --> 00:50:26,480
Sit down. Let me check you.

464
00:50:28,000 --> 00:50:28,960
Slowly.

465
00:50:35,760 --> 00:50:37,840
Does your heart still hurt?

466
00:50:39,720 --> 00:50:40,880
No.

467
00:50:44,200 --> 00:50:46,000
Has Yiam been overworking you?

468
00:50:47,880 --> 00:50:49,840
He barely lets me lift a finger.

469
00:50:52,800 --> 00:50:55,000
Could it be your monthly cycle?

470
00:50:56,960 --> 00:50:59,880
No, my monthly cycle
hasn't come for three months.

471
00:51:01,920 --> 00:51:05,800
Yiam, what kind of healer are you?
Can't you tell?

472
00:51:12,360 --> 00:51:13,400
Or is it…?

473
00:51:15,080 --> 00:51:16,320
Your wife is pregnant.

474
00:51:20,600 --> 00:51:21,680
Yiwha…

475
00:51:24,160 --> 00:51:26,040
I'm going to be a father.

476
00:51:37,160 --> 00:51:39,160
ONE YEAR LATER

477
00:52:46,920 --> 00:52:50,400
You must have seen Lasor already, right?

478
00:53:30,000 --> 00:53:31,040
I am ready.

479
00:53:52,040 --> 00:53:55,320
Since Monk Lasor passed
from jungle fever last year,

480
00:53:56,280 --> 00:53:58,200
does your heart still ache?

481
00:53:59,720 --> 00:54:01,480
I'm fine.

482
00:54:02,320 --> 00:54:04,280
I only pity him.

483
00:54:04,360 --> 00:54:07,440
Though he redeemed himself,

484
00:54:09,120 --> 00:54:11,480
he could not escape karma,

485
00:54:13,160 --> 00:54:15,080
like Angulimala.

486
00:54:17,400 --> 00:54:22,960
I feared I would lose you too,
as Grandma Chi Pa Khao foretold.

487
00:54:24,360 --> 00:54:26,600
Perhaps Manee and Manat,

488
00:54:26,680 --> 00:54:29,360
our twins, saved me.

489
00:54:30,880 --> 00:54:33,600
Their two little hearts

490
00:54:33,680 --> 00:54:35,880
kept mine beating

491
00:54:36,720 --> 00:54:38,680
so I could live on as their mother.

492
00:54:41,360 --> 00:54:45,200
At last, the darkness has passed.

493
00:54:46,560 --> 00:54:48,960
The new governor from the capital

494
00:54:49,040 --> 00:54:51,760
is said to be righteous,

495
00:54:52,840 --> 00:54:56,840
bringing peace and prosperity.

496
00:54:57,880 --> 00:55:00,400
<i>His Excellency wrote that</i>

497
00:55:00,480 --> 00:55:03,320
<i>Phraya Ratsadanupradit Mahisorn Pakdee</i>

498
00:55:03,400 --> 00:55:06,440
<i>observed how well rubber thrived</i>
<i>among the Malays</i>

499
00:55:06,520 --> 00:55:10,600
<i>and conceived the idea</i>
<i>of planting it in Siam.</i>

500
00:55:10,680 --> 00:55:14,120
<i>I heard Western plantation owners</i>

501
00:55:14,200 --> 00:55:15,680
<i>were very protective of their trees.</i>

502
00:55:15,760 --> 00:55:18,840
<i>Yes. But in the end,</i>
<i>Phraya Sathol Sathanphithak,</i>

503
00:55:18,920 --> 00:55:20,320
<i>his nephew,</i>

504
00:55:20,400 --> 00:55:23,000
<i>managed to bring</i>
<i>the seedlings by steamship</i>

505
00:55:23,080 --> 00:55:25,760
<i>to be planted in Kantang.</i>

506
00:55:26,440 --> 00:55:29,160
Rubber will become a valuable crop,

507
00:55:29,800 --> 00:55:33,720
creating jobs and income
for the southern provinces.

508
00:55:33,800 --> 00:55:35,240
People will be able
to earn a living on their own.

509
00:55:38,600 --> 00:55:39,880
I believe it now.

510
00:55:40,720 --> 00:55:42,960
Siam will never lack good people.

511
00:55:44,360 --> 00:55:47,120
Every land has both good and bad.

512
00:55:47,640 --> 00:55:50,600
We must support the good in doing good,

513
00:55:51,400 --> 00:55:53,480
and restrain the wicked

514
00:55:53,560 --> 00:55:56,400
from causing harm.

515
00:56:02,040 --> 00:56:04,440
Yiam! There's trouble!

516
00:56:04,960 --> 00:56:05,960
What is it?

517
00:56:06,040 --> 00:56:07,440
- Robby!
- Huh?

518
00:56:07,520 --> 00:56:09,280
I mean, robbery.

519
00:56:09,360 --> 00:56:10,800
A peddler's been attacked.

520
00:56:14,480 --> 00:56:16,640
Chang, watch my child.

521
00:56:17,360 --> 00:56:18,360
I'm coming too.

522
00:56:19,680 --> 00:56:21,160
- Where?
- Behind the market.

523
00:56:22,320 --> 00:56:25,760
Pun, why are you still here?
You're a police officer.

524
00:56:26,400 --> 00:56:28,240
Right. I'm going.

525
00:56:32,040 --> 00:56:33,200
Yiam.

526
00:56:33,280 --> 00:56:35,240
<i>As long as this land</i>
<i>still faces injustice,</i>

527
00:56:35,320 --> 00:56:36,800
<i>Yiwha and I</i>

528
00:56:36,880 --> 00:56:39,200
<i>will continue to fight for what is right.</i>

529
00:57:01,080 --> 00:57:04,040
THE END

530
00:57:46,800 --> 00:57:50,400
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
